       "</table><p>... and 593 more row(s).</p></details></details><div style=\"margin-left: 0px;\" class=\"container-fields\"><span class=\"field-key\" title=\".experiment_description\">experiment_description: </span><span class=\"field-value\">Wireless Neuropixels recordings from the hippocampus of freely flying Egyptian fruit bats (Rousettus aegyptiacus) engaged in rewarded spontaneous aerial foraging. Bats flew freely in an indoor or outdoor enclosure between two automated feeders. We simultaneously recorded ensemble activity from putative single neurons and the local field potential (LFP) from dorsal hippocampus (CA1/CA3) while bats spontaneously alternated between rest and flight. During rest, time-compressed forward and reverse replays of multiple flight trajectories coincided with sharp-wave ripples. During flight, neural ensembles exhibited fast representational sweeps phase-locked to the wing-beat cycle rather than theta oscillations. Associated publication: Forli, Fan, Qi & Yartsev, Nature 2025.\n",
       "</span></div><div style=\"margin-left: 0px;\" class=\"container-fields\"><span class=\"field-key\" title=\".session_id\">session_id: </span><span class=\"field-value\">Dataset_3_14543_240419</span></div><div style=\"margin-left: 0px;\" class=\"container-fields\"><span class=\"field-key\" title=\".lab\">lab: </span><span class=\"field-value\">Yartsev Lab</span></div><div style=\"margin-left: 0px;\" class=\"container-fields\"><span class=\"field-key\" title=\".institution\">institution: </span><span class=\"field-value\">University of California, Berkeley</span></div><div style=\"margin-left: 0px;\" class=\"container-fields\"><span class=\"field-key\" title=\".source_script\">source_script: </span><span class=\"field-value\">Created using NeuroConv v0.9.3</span></div><div style=\"margin-left: 0px;\" class=\"container-fields\"><span class=\"field-key\" title=\".source_script_file_name\">source_script_file_name: </span><span class=\"field-value\">/opt/anaconda3/envs/yartsev_lab_to_nwb_env/lib/python3.13/site-packages/neuroconv/basedatainterface.py</span></div></div>"
